Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of 1-Butyl-3-methylimidazolium Tetrafluoroborate + H2O Binary Mixtures from (303.15 to 353.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of water (1) + 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate (2) were measured over the entire mole fraction range from (303.15 to 353.15) K. From these data, excess molar volumes (VE), and viscosity deviations () were calculated. The VE and  were fitted to the Redlich-Kister equation using a multiparametric nonlinear regression method. Estimated coefficients of the Redlich-Kister equation and standard deviation calculated from the Redlich-Kister equation to the experimental data are also presented. The results show that the densities and viscosities are dependent strongly on water content. Comparatively, the viscosity deviation  is more sensitive to temperature than the excess molar volume VE.
sKeyword: Densities and viscosities of water + 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate
